  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA60-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu ciṟaippuṟamāka uḻavaṟkuc colluvāḷāyt tōḻi ceṟippaṟivuṟīiyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidant informed [him] of [her] confinement, being one who speaks to the ploughman while [HE] is behind the fence.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA60">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            malaikaṇ ṭaṉṉa nilaipuṇar nivappiṟ</l>
<l>            peruneṟ palkūṭ ṭerumai yuḻava</l>
<l>            kaṇpaṭai peṟāatu taṇpular viṭiyaṟ</l>
<l>            karuṅkaṇ varāaṟ peruntaṭi miḷirvaiyoṭu</l>
<l>            pukarvai yaricip pommaṟ peruñcōṟu </l>
<l>            kavarpaṭu kaiyai kaḻuma mānti</l>
<l>            nīruṟuc ceṟuvi ṉāṟumuṭi yaḻuttaniṉ</l>
<l>            ṉaṭuna roṭunī cēṟi yāyiṉvaṇ</l>
<l>            cāyu neytalu mōmpumati yemmiṉ</l>
<l>            māyiruṅ kūntaṉ maṭantai </l>
<l>            kāyvaḷaik kūṭṭu maṇiyumā ravaiyē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>O ploughman</l>
<l>with [your] buffalos by the many granaries of great paddy,</l>
<l rend="indent">in height combining with [their] the base as if one saw a mountain,</l>
<l rend="indent2">at cool dawning dawn where one doesn't obtain sleep,</l>
<l>o you with a hand that happens to(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">kavar paṭu</term>: do we have to take <term xml:lang="ta">paṭu</term> as an auxiliary here, perhaps in a passive construction that has not yet frozen into regular combination with an infinitive?</note> seize</l>
<l rend="indent3">thick big cooked rice, in stained(?), sharp grains,</l>
<l rend="indent3">with the sauce of the plentiful flesh of the black-eyed murrel,</l>
<l rend="indent2">if you, having fed copiously, go with your planters,</l>
<l rend="indent">who have put down fragrant bundles in the water-rich fields,</l>
<l>beware of [hurting] the blue waterlilies that are widely emaciated<note place="foot">T.V.G. takes <term xml:lang="ta">cāy</term> as referring to a kind of grass used by girls to fashion dolls, which is not backed up by the lexica (see however KT 276.2 for <term xml:lang="ta">pañcāy</term>). So then it would be Cāy grass and Neytal flowers that should not be weeded.</note>.</l>
<l>In our house they do adorn, in union with shining bangles,</l>
<l rend="indent3">the girls with long dark tresses.</l>
        </lg>
         </div>
